Package com.microsoft.identity.client

Provides the classes necessary to create a client for azure active directory to get tokens.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AuthenticationCallback
    Callback to use with token request.
    ILoggerCallback
    Interface for apps to configure the external logging and implement the callback to designate the customize place for where to output the log messages.
    MsalEventReceiver
    The interface function for apps to override if they want to get the Telemetry from MSAL.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AuthenticationActivity
    Custom tab requires the device to have a browser with custom tab support, chrome with version >= 45 comes with the support and is available on all devices with API version >= 16 .
    AuthenticationResult
    MSAL success authentication result.
    BrowserTabActivity
    MSAL activity class(needs to be public to be discoverable by the os) to get the redirect with code from authorize endpoint.
    Logger
    MSAL Logger for diagnostic purpose.
    PublicClientApplication
    Entry point for developer to create the public native application, and make API call to get token.
    Telemetry
    Collects and publishes telemetry key/value pairs to subscribers.
    User
    Contains the detailed info to identify an user.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Logger.LogLevel
    Enum class for LogLevel that the sdk recognizes.
    UiBehavior
    The UI options that developer could pass in during interactive sign in.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    MsalClientException
    This exception class represents general errors that are local to the library.
    MsalException
    MsalException that will be thrown or sent back via callback, represents the detailed exception thrown by the sdk.
    MsalServiceException
    This exception class represents errors when communicating to service, could be from authorize endpoint or token endpoint.
    MsalUiRequiredException
    This exception class is to inform developers that UI is required for authentication to succeed.
